00:55:56,740 --> 00:56:00,420
Does it speak?

497
00:56:00,820 --> 00:56:06,220
We are in a situation
that is beyond morality. Hm?

498
00:56:06,260 --> 00:56:08,980
Your wife is dead.

499
00:56:09,220 --> 00:56:14,500
How do you know? How can you be definitive
about a construct you do not understand?

500
00:56:14,740 --> 00:56:17,300
She's a copy. A facsimile.

501
00:56:17,540 --> 00:56:20,740
And she's seducing you all over again.

502
00:56:20,980 --> 00:56:24,620
You're sick.

503
00:56:27,860 --> 00:56:32,060
We are not taking her back with us.

504
00:57:42,580 --> 00:57:46,260
Leave the light off.

505
00:57:57,540 --> 00:58:01,220
You think you're dreaming me.

506
00:58:01,460 --> 00:58:03,380
You're not Gibarian.

507
00:58:03,620 --> 00:58:06,180
No?

508
00:58:06,420 --> 00:58:09,460
Who am I, then?

509
00:58:09,700 --> 00:58:12,340
- A puppet.
- And you're not?

510
00:58:12,580 --> 00:58:14,900
Well, maybe you're my puppet.

511
00:58:15,140 --> 00:58:18,740
But like all puppets,
you think you're actually human.

512
00:58:18,980 --> 00:58:23,460
That's the puppet's dream - being human.

513
00:58:28,420 --> 00:58:31,140
Why did you kill yourself?

514
00:58:31,380 --> 00:58:35,060
It seemed like a good idea
at the time. Now I think I made a mistake.

515
00:58:35,300 --> 00:58:39,540
- What about your son?
- That's not my son. My son is on Earth.

516
00:58:39,780 --> 00:58:46,060
And that's not your wife.
They are part of Solaris. Remember that.

517
00:58:49,380 --> 00:58:52,180
What does Solaris want from us?

518
00:58:52,420 --> 00:58:55,700
Why do you think it has to want something?

519
00:58:55,940 --> 00:59:01,540
This is why you have to leave.
If you keep thinking there is a solution...

520
00:59:01,780 --> 00:59:04,100
you'll die here.

521
00:59:04,340 --> 00:59:08,100
I can't leave her.

522
00:59:08,100 --> 00:59:09,540
I'll figure it out.

523
00:59:09,780 --> 00:59:12,580
Do you understand
what I'm trying to tell you?

524
00:59:12,820 --> 00:59:15,140
There are no answers.

525
00:59:15,380 --> 00:59:19,020
Only choices.

526
00:59:37,620 --> 00:59:40,900
Rheya?

527
00:59:46,580 --> 00:59:49,860
Rheya?

528
01:00:00,420 --> 01:00:03,660
Rheya?

529
01:00:20,820 --> 01:00:24,100
Rheya?

530
01:00:30,100 --> 01:00:33,540
Gordon!

531
01:01:12,020 --> 01:01:17,020
- What happened?
- She drank liquid oxygen.

532
01:01:39,540 --> 01:01:43,020
She's dead.

533
01:01:43,700 --> 01:01:46,580
No.

534
01:02:06,660 --> 01:02:12,900
I never get used to them.
These... resurrections.

535
01:03:08,900 --> 01:03:12,340
Oh, no.

536
01:03:12,900 --> 01:03:16,180
No.

537
01:03:21,300 --> 01:03:25,180
Why'd you do that?

538
01:03:25,940 --> 01:03:27,140
Rheya?

539
01:03:27,380 --> 01:03:31,220
Don't call me that.

540
01:03:38,180 --> 01:03:40,740
<i>There are two components.</i>

541
01:03:40,980 --> 01:03:46,820
A high-energy proton accelerator
and a matter phase modulator.

542
01:03:47,060 --> 01:03:52,820
By adjusting the tuning frequency I get an
enhancement of Higgs antibosons at 90GHz

543
01:03:53,060 --> 01:03:56,980
and an almost pure beam at 160GHz.

544
01:03:57,220 --> 01:04:01,060
I used it on mine.

545
01:04:01,300 --> 01:04:03,060
What happens?

546
01:04:03,300 --> 01:04:08,140
They disappear,
back where they came from.

547
01:04:11,220 --> 01:04:14,980
It's what she wants.

548
01:04:15,380 --> 01:04:19,220
I won't let her do it.

549
01:04:19,300 --> 01:04:23,780
She'll come to me when you're asleep.

550
01:04:25,380 --> 01:04:29,340
Then I won't sleep.

551
01:04:31,060 --> 01:04:33,860
<i>Don't you see?
I came from your memory of her.</i>

552
01:04:34,100 --> 01:04:38,100
<i>That's the problem. I'm not a whole person.</i>

553
01:04:38,340 --> 01:04:42,820
In your memory
you get to control everything.

554
01:04:42,900 --> 01:04:47,540
So even if you remember something wrong,
I am predetermined to carry it out.

555
01:04:47,780 --> 01:04:50,100
I'm suicidal because
that's how you remember me.

556
01:04:50,340 --> 01:04:54,660
My voice sounds the way it does
because that's how you remember it.

557
01:04:54,900 --> 01:04:59,060
I don't believe that we're
predetermined to relive our past.

558
01:04:59,300 --> 01:05:03,540
I think that we can choose to do it differently.

559
01:05:03,780 --> 01:05:10,260
The day I left and you said you wouldn't make
it, I didn't hear you because I was angry.

560
01:05:10,500 --> 01:05:14,020
This is my chance to undo that mistake.

561
01:05:14,260 --> 01:05:16,660
And I need you to help me.

562
01:05:16,900 --> 01:05:21,100
But am I really Rheya?

563
01:05:24,340 --> 01:05:27,220
I don't know any more.

564
01:05:27,460 --> 01:05:31,820
All I see is you.

565
01:06:02,020 --> 01:06:05,860
All I see is you.

566
01:06:09,300 --> 01:06:12,940
It created me.

567
01:06:13,380 --> 01:06:17,660
And yet I can't communicate with it.

568
01:06:19,060 --> 01:06:21,620
It must hear me, though.

569
01:06:21,860 --> 01:06:26,140
It must know what's happening to me.

570
01:06:26,340 --> 01:06:30,420
And you and I, we would
have to have some kind of...

571
01:06:30,660 --> 01:06:34,700
an arrangement, some kind of...

572
01:06:38,020 --> 01:06:41,620
unspoken understanding...

573
01:06:41,860 --> 01:06:45,900
that I'm not really a human being.

574
01:06:47,700 --> 01:06:51,180
No, Rheya.

575
01:06:55,060 --> 01:06:56,980
Chris...

576
01:06:57,220 --> 01:07:01,220
Chris, I wish you would just
let them use the device on me.

577
01:07:01,460 --> 01:07:08,820
And then you can go back to Earth
and you can tell everybody all about Solaris.

578
01:07:10,740 --> 01:07:12,740
No.

579
01:07:12,980 --> 01:07:17,860
It's the only solution that makes any sense.

580
01:07:18,180 --> 01:07:22,100
We could never have
a life together on Earth, Chris.

581
01:07:22,340 --> 01:07:25,780
You know that.

582
01:07:25,940 --> 01:07:28,980
It would be impossible.

583
01:07:29,220 --> 01:07:33,380
And this? What kind of life is this?

584
01:07:33,620 --> 01:07:35,380
Trapped here.

585
01:07:35,620 --> 01:07:38,820
It's not a life.

586
01:07:39,060 --> 01:07:41,540
I don't know what to call it.

587
01:07:41,780 --> 01:07:45,060
It's what we have.

588
01:07:45,300 --> 01:07:47,300
It's enough for me.

589
01:07:47,540 --> 01:07:50,100
You need to rest.

590
01:07:50,340 --> 01:07:54,180
You're going to make yourself ill.

591
01:07:54,420 --> 01:07:59,780
- I don't care.
- Just lie down for a moment.

592
01:08:00,020 --> 01:08:01,700
Please, Chris.

593
01:08:01,940 --> 01:08:05,580
You have to rest.

594
01:08:33,220 --> 01:08:37,380
You know I'm not human
so I don't understand what you're afraid of.

595
01:08:37,620 --> 01:08:39,860
Of course you can use the device.

596
01:08:40,100 --> 01:08:43,380
It's not murder. You said that yourself.

597
01:08:43,620 --> 01:08:47,060
You're the one who had
the idea in the first place.

598
01:08:47,300 --> 01:08:51,380
Chris doesn't trust me. He...

599
01:13:32,180 --> 01:13:37,220
<i>Chris, don't blame Gordon.</i>

600
01:13:37,940 --> 01:13:42,380
<i>It's not her fault. I begged her to do it.</i>

601
01:13:43,140 --> 01:13:46,180
<i>It's better this way.</i>

602
01:13:46,420 --> 01:13:49,300
<i>I found the suicide note.</i>

603
01:13:49,540 --> 01:13:52,500
<i>I went through your things.</i>

604
01:13:52,740 --> 01:13:56,820
<i>The page torn from the book of poems.</i>

605
01:13:57,060 --> 01:14:00,860
<i>And I realised...</i>

606
01:14:00,940 --> 01:14:02,660
<i>I'm not her.</i>

607
01:14:02,900 --> 01:14:06,340
<i>I'm not Rheya.</i>

608
01:14:06,460 --> 01:14:09,380
<i>I know you loved me, though.</i>

609
01:14:09,620 --> 01:14:12,820
<i>I know that. I felt that.</i>

610
01:14:13,060 --> 01:14:15,460
<i>And I love you.</i>

611
01:14:15,700 --> 01:14:20,820
<i>I wish we could just
live inside that feeling forever.</i>

612
01:14:21,460 --> 01:14:25,380
<i>Maybe there's a place where we can.</i>

613
01:14:25,620 --> 01:14:27,740
<i>But I know it's not on Earth.</i>

614
01:14:27,980 --> 01:14:31,860
<i>And it's not on this ship.</i>

615
01:14:33,140 --> 01:14:37,060
<i>That's all I can say right now.</i>

616
01:14:57,900 --> 01:14:59,300
- You killed her!
- Not her. It.

617
01:14:59,540 --> 01:15:03,220
- It's murder!
- Kelvin, she begged me. It wasn't painful.

618
01:15:03,460 --> 01:15:04,700
- She'll be back!
- No.

619
01:15:04,940 --> 01:15:07,540
- Why would you let her do it?!
- Kelvin!

620
01:15:07,780 --> 01:15:09,540
It's not human!

621
01:15:09,780 --> 01:15:14,020
Whatever it is, it's not human,
and I'm threatened by that.

622
01:15:14,260 --> 01:15:16,900
And I wanna win. I want humans to win.

623
01:15:17,140 --> 01:15:20,940
Whose side are you on?

624
01:15:21,060 --> 01:15:27,500
- What are you doing?
- Putting the Al back online. I'm going home.

625
01:15:40,580 --> 01:15:43,820
Gordon.

626
01:15:45,060 --> 01:15:48,300
Gordon!

627
01:16:10,740 --> 01:16:14,180
- I knew it.
- How long you think he's been dead?

628
01:16:14,420 --> 01:16:18,860
Hard to say because of the cold.

629
01:16:18,980 --> 01:16:22,660
He attacked me.

630
01:16:24,020 --> 01:16:27,300
There I am. Somehow, there I am.

631
01:16:27,540 --> 01:16:33,060
And I couldn't tell you how I'm there,
or who I am or what's going on.

632
01:16:33,300 --> 01:16:36,660
But before I can get to that,

633
01:16:36,900 --> 01:16:39,060
what's this over here?

634
01:16:39,300 --> 01:16:42,740
Comin' at me. What...
what are you tryin' to do?

635
01:16:42,980 --> 01:16:45,940
Oh, I see. You're tryin' to kill me.

636
01:16:46,180 --> 01:16:50,020
Yeah, confusing. I'll tell you somethin'
confusing. Bingo, there you are,

637
01:16:50,260 --> 01:16:53,740
and my welcoming committee
dropped his knife and it's good night.

638
01:16:53,980 --> 01:16:58,100
And, oh, by the way, after all that I find, uh...

639
01:16:58,340 --> 01:17:02,900
this, uh, whoever this... I get my first
good look at it and it happens to be...

640
01:17:03,140 --> 01:17:06,020
I survive the first 30 seconds of this...

641
01:17:06,260 --> 01:17:10,020
life, whatever you wanna call it...
by killing someone.

642
01:17:10,260 --> 01:17:15,500
And, oh, ah, by killing someone
who happens to be me.

643
01:17:15,540 --> 01:17:20,420
See, most people... I would think most people
in this position would be, like "This... ah."

644
01:17:20,660 --> 01:17:25,180
"I don't know." However, this is at least...
This is an incredible opportunity.

645
01:17:25,420 --> 01:17:28,900
This is... What if this is a gift? I'm a gift.

646
01:17:29,140 --> 01:17:32,620
Hey.

647
01:17:34,660 --> 01:17:38,900
I say we use the Higgs device on him.

648
01:17:42,260 --> 01:17:44,500
Mm. Mm-mm.

649
01:17:44,740 --> 01:17:49,340
I don't think you really have time.

650
01:17:49,620 --> 01:17:53,380
Why would you say that?

651
01:17:53,420 --> 01:17:56,740
Well, you know, ever since
we used the famous Higgs device,

652
01:17:56,980 --> 01:18:01,860
Solaris started taking on mass exponentially.

653
01:18:01,980 --> 01:18:06,100
You might have noticed
how we're a lot closer to it.

654
01:18:06,340 --> 01:18:10,340
That would be because everything
within its gravitational field -

655
01:18:10,580 --> 01:18:14,420
it's pulling it in.

656
01:18:14,940 --> 01:18:17,060
Ah, and, yeah, sorry. By the way,

657
01:18:17,300 --> 01:18:23,380
the Higgs device also
drained the fuel cell reactors.

658
01:18:26,940 --> 01:18:30,700
Uh, if... Can I make a suggestion?

659
01:18:30,940 --> 01:18:35,700
I mean, this is... You can do what you want,
but I would just lock me in here really tight

660
01:18:35,940 --> 01:18:40,020
and take the "Athena" back.

661
01:18:42,340 --> 01:18:46,260
Wear your seat belt.

662
01:19:40,980 --> 01:19:43,380
Switch to internal power.

663
01:19:43,620 --> 01:19:46,900
Start fuel cell operational diagnostic.

664
01:19:47,140 --> 01:19:50,020
Service check on LGA.

665
01:19:50,260 --> 01:19:53,220
Point and calibrate high-beam antenna.

666
01:19:53,460 --> 01:19:56,980
Depressurising. Spin all turbines to standby.

667
01:19:57,220 --> 01:20:00,500
Disengage coupling interlocks
and all docking couplers.

668
01:20:00,740 --> 01:20:05,500
Vent and seal
all main engine propellant lines.

669
01:20:21,220 --> 01:20:23,740
<i>Earth.</i>

670
01:20:23,980 --> 01:20:27,660
<i>Even the word sounded strange to me now.</i>

671
01:20:27,900 --> 01:20:31,380
<i>Unfamiliar.</i>

672
01:20:33,540 --> 01:20:36,580
<i>How long had I been gone?</i>

673
01:20:36,820 --> 01:20:39,860
<i>How long had I been back?</i>

674
01:20:40,100 --> 01:20:43,740
<i>Did it matter?</i>

675
01:20:46,820 --> 01:20:52,100
<i>I tried to find the rhythm
of the world where I used to live.</i>

676
01:20:52,340 --> 01:20:55,180
<i>I followed the current.</i>

677
01:20:55,420 --> 01:20:59,140
<i>I was silent and attentive.</i>

678
01:20:59,380 --> 01:21:02,900
<i>I made a conscious effort to smile...</i>

679
01:21:03,140 --> 01:21:05,060
<i>nod...</i>

680
01:21:05,300 --> 01:21:07,620
<i>stand...</i>

681
01:21:07,860 --> 01:21:14,100
<i>and perform the millions of gestures
that constitute life on Earth.</i>

682
01:21:15,620 --> 01:21:21,300
<i>I studied these gestures
until they became reflexes again.</i>

683
01:21:22,740 --> 01:21:25,380
<i>But I was haunted by the idea</i>

684
01:21:25,620 --> 01:21:29,540
<i>that I remembered her wrong.</i>

685
01:21:31,700 --> 01:21:36,180
<i>That somehow I was wrong about everything.</i>

686
01:22:36,940 --> 01:22:41,700
Depressurising.
Spin all turbines to standby.

687
01:22:41,940 --> 01:22:45,740
Disengage coupling interlocks
and all docking couplers.

688
01:22:45,980 --> 01:22:50,780
Vent and seal
all main engine propellant lines.

689
01:23:51,220 --> 01:23:53,780
Rheya!

690
01:24:01,140 --> 01:24:04,580
Rheya?

691
01:26:12,020 --> 01:26:15,500
Chris?

692
01:26:15,860 --> 01:26:19,100
Chris?

693
01:26:57,060 --> 01:27:01,300
Am I alive... or dead?

694
01:27:03,420 --> 01:27:07,860
We don't have to think like that any more.

695
01:27:10,340 --> 01:27:14,100
We're together now.

696
01:27:15,220 --> 01:27:19,220
Everything we've done is forgiven.

697
01:27:19,460 --> 01:27:22,700
Everything.

